## Why This Is Asked

Tests the ability to design Kubernetes-native controls for multi-tenant, CI-heavy workloads, focusing on per-namespace isolation, clean lifecycle management with finalizers, and comprehensive observability.

## Key Concepts

- CustomResourceDefinition and controller reconcile loop patterns
- Per-namespace NetworkPolicy generation and cleanup automation
- Finalizers guaranteeing cleanup after policy removal
- Observability through status fields and Prometheus metrics
- Multi-tenant security isolation in shared Kubernetes environments

## Code Example

```javascript
// Pseudo-reconcile flow for EphemeralTenantPolicy
async function reconcile(policy) {
  if (!policy.finalizers.includes('ephemeral.cleanup')) {
    // Add finalizer to ensure cleanup
    policy.finalizers.push('ephemeral.cleanup');
  }

  // Create or update NetworkPolicy for CI isolation
  const networkPolicy = generateNetworkPolicy(policy);
  await applyNetworkPolicy(networkPolicy);

  // Update status and emit metrics
  updatePolicyStatus(policy, 'Active');
  emitMetrics('policy_reconciled', policy.name);
}
```

