## Why This Is Asked

Test practical upgrade strategies for stateful apps, focusing on replica-set dynamics, Kubernetes upgrade mechanics, and data safety during in-place upgrades.

## Key Concepts

- StatefulSet updateStrategy RollingUpdate and partition to control upgrade order
- MongoDB replica set health, replSetGetStatus, and primary elections
- Data durability with persistent volumes and upgrading without data loss
- Canary and traffic validation during upgrade

## Code Example

```javascript
// Example Node.js snippet to check status and optionally trigger stepDown
const { MongoClient } = require('mongodb');
async function status(uri){
  const c = await MongoClient.connect(uri, { useNewUrlParser: true, useUnifiedTopology: true });
  const admin = c.db('admin');
  const st = await admin.command({ replSetGetStatus: 1 });
  console.log(st);
  // if primary, trigger stepDown
  if (st.myState === 1) {
    await admin.command({ replSetStepDown: 60, secondaryCatchUpPeriodSecs: 30 });
  }
  await c.close();
}
```

## Follow-up Questions

- What if a member fails to start after upgrade, how would you recover?
- How would you scale the replica set beyond 3 members while preserving upgrade safety?

## Why This Is Asked

This question probes the ability to design a robust cross-namespace orchestration primitive, with DAG scheduling, idempotent reconciliation, and cleanup semantics. It also touches RBAC, metrics, and testing at scale.

## Key Concepts

- CustomResourceDefinition and controller patterns
- DAG scheduling and dependency resolution
- Per-namespace isolation and quotas
- Idempotent reconciler design
- Finalizers and cleanup lifecycle
- Observability: conditions, events, metrics across namespaces
- Backoff strategies with jitter

## Code Example

```javascript
// Pseudo reconciler structure
async function reconcile(dataMigrationPlan) {
  // Parse DAG and identify ready tasks
  const readyTasks = parseDAG(dataMigrationPlan.spec.tasks);

  for (const task of readyTasks) {
    // Check idempotency
    if (await jobExists(task.name)) {
      continue;
    }

    // Create Job with backoff strategy
    await createJob(task);

    // Add finalizer for cleanup
    await addFinalizer(dataMigrationPlan, task.name);
  }

  // Update status and conditions
  await updateStatus(dataMigrationPlan);
}
```

