## Expected Answer
Strong candidates will discuss: controller-runtime patterns, workqueue management, finalizers for cleanup, watch bookmarks for efficiency, backoff strategies, resource quotas, and proper event filtering to reduce reconciliation noise.

## Code Example
```typescript
func (r *MicroserviceReconciler) Reconcile(ctx context.Context, req ctrl.Request) (ctrl.Result, error) {
    // Use workqueue with rate limiting
    if !r.queue.CanAdd() {
        return ctrl.Result{RequeueAfter: time.Second * 5}, nil
    }

    // Implement finalizer pattern
    if !microservice.ObjectMeta.DeletionTimestamp.IsZero() {
        if containsString(microservice.ObjectMeta.Finalizers, myFinalizerName) {
            // Cleanup logic
            return r.cleanup(ctx, microservice)
        }
        return ctrl.Result{}, nil
    }

    // Efficient reconciliation with selective updates
    return r.reconcileWithSelectiveUpdate(ctx, microservice)
}
```

